  • Classes in com.poesys.db.dao.insert used by com.poesys.db.dao 
    Class and Description
    IInsert
    An interface for a Command pattern class that inserts an object or link into the database based on values in a data transfer object (DTO).
    IInsertBatch
    An interface for a Command pattern class that inserts a collection of objects into the database in batches with a specified batch size.
    IInsertCollection
    An interface for a Command pattern class that inserts a collection of objects into the database in one group.
    IInsertSql
    An interface that defines the set of operations required by an IInsert or IInsertBatch object to build a SQL INSERT statement for a data transfer object (DTO).

    An implementation of the IInsertBatch generic interface that contains the base code for inserting a batch of objects into the database.

    InsertNoKeyCollection
    An implementation of the IInsertCollection generic interface that contains the base code for inserting a collection of objects that do not contain primary key values (identity or auto-generated keys) into the database.
